This paper deals with the problem of mining association rules in large datasets, which is a classic problem in data mining and falls under the scope of several CS sub-categories. The use of interestingness measures such as confidence and conviction suggests that this paper is likely to be related to machine learning and data mining (cs.LG), while the focus on multidimensional datasets and the requirement for items to have a common attribute suggests that it may also be related to databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The potential applications in marketing, medical, financial, and predictive maintenance domains suggest that this paper may also be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
